      <entry xml:id="entry_margas" xml:lang="os" abv:completeness="complete">
        <form type="lemma"><orth>margas</orth></form>
        <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>съестные продукты, приносимые родственниками и знакомыми умершего на поминки</q>
            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>food brought to the funeral by relatives and acquaintances of the deceased</q>
            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>поминки, справляемые родственниками в доме покойника непосредственно после
                смерти</q>
            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>funerary feast organized by relatives in the house of the deceased just after the
                deceased’s death</q>
            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
        <exampleGrp xmlns="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict">
          <example>
            <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">dy ta kædæm cæwys? mænæ <oRef>margas</oRef>
              xæssyn… xorz waid æmæ rūxs k˳y zæǧikkat mardæn</quote>
            <tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">а ты куда идешь? — вот несу <oRef/>; было бы
                хорошо, если бы вы сказали <foreign><ref type="xr" target="#entry_rūxs"
                  >ruxs</ref></foreign> (поминовение) покойнику</q>
            </tr>
            <tr xml:lang="en">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">and where are you going? — well, I am bringing
                the <oRef/>; it would be good if you said <foreign><ref type="xr"
                    target="#entry_rūxs">ruxs</ref></foreign> (commemoration) to the deceased</q>
            </tr>
            <bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/>
              <biblScope>III 87</biblScope></bibl>
          </example>
        </exampleGrp>
        <etym xml:lang="ru">Вероятно, восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
            <phr type="rec">marka+asa</phr>
            <gloss><q>трапеза (<mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">asa-</w></mentioned>) смерти
                  (<mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">marka-</w></mentioned>)</q></gloss>,
                <gloss><q>поминки</q></gloss></mentioned>. В первой части <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
            <w type="rec">marka-</w>
            <gloss><q>смерть</q></gloss></mentioned> (см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_marg"
            >выше</ref>); во второй— <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">asa-</w>
            <gloss><q>еда</q></gloss></mentioned> от <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">as-</w>
            <gloss><q>есть</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>кушать</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. такие
          образования, как <mentioned xml:lang="inc-x-old"><lang/>
            <w>prātarāśa-</w>
            <gloss><q>утренняя еда</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inc-x-old"
              ><w>sāyamāsa-</w>
            <gloss><q>вечерняя еда</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. также <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_mīnas" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
            <w>mīnas</w>
            <gloss><q>угощение</q></gloss></ref>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bas"><w>bas</w>
            <gloss><q>суп</q></gloss>
            <note xml:lang="ru" type="comment">(← <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><phr type="rec"
                  >upa+asa</phr></mentioned>)</note></ref>. Сложение
            <oRef>marg-as</oRef> образовалось тогда, когда <ref type="xr" target="#entry_marg"
              ><w>marg</w> (← <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">marka-</w></mentioned>)</ref>
          означало еще <gloss><q>смерть</q></gloss>, не получив более специального значения
              <gloss><q>яд</q></gloss>.</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">Probably derived from <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
            <phr type="rec">marka+asa</phr>
            <gloss><q>meal (<mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">asa-</w></mentioned>) of death
                  (<mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">marka-</w></mentioned>)</q></gloss>,
                <gloss><q>funerary feast</q></gloss></mentioned>. In the former part <mentioned
            xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
            <w type="rec">marka-</w>
            <gloss><q>death</q></gloss></mentioned> (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_marg"
            >above</ref>); in the latter, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">asa-</w>
            <gloss><q>food</q></gloss></mentioned> from <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec"
              >as-</w>
            <gloss><q>eat</q></gloss></mentioned>; cf. also such derivates as <mentioned
            xml:lang="inc-x-old"><lang/>
            <w>prātarāśa-</w>
            <gloss><q>morning meal</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inc-x-old"
              ><w>sāyamāsa-</w>
            <gloss><q>evening meal</q></gloss></mentioned>; cf. also <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_mīnas" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
            <w>mīnas</w>
            <gloss><q>food given to guest</q></gloss></ref>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bas"
              ><w>bas</w>
            <gloss><q>soup</q></gloss>
            <note xml:lang="en" type="comment">(← <mentioned
                xml:lang="ira"><phr type="rec">upa+asa</phr></mentioned>)</note></ref>. The compound
            <oRef>marg-as</oRef> was formed at a time when <ref type="xr" target="#entry_marg"
              ><w>marg</w> (← <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec">marka-</w></mentioned>)</ref>
          still meant <gloss><q>death</q></gloss>, not having yet received its special meaning
              <gloss><q>poison</q></gloss>.</etym>
      </entry>
